Stop Wasting Money on LinkedIn Premium, Use these Free tools instead...

- Find Emails Hiring managers and Startup founders to connect directly using PhantomBuster

- Write Cold DM or Email for recruiters, Hiring managers using Network AI by Wonsulting

- Get a free LinkedIn or Resume review using Hiration

- Find Recruiter Email on Linkedin using RocketReach

- Tailor your Resume with Job Description using JobScan

- Use LinkedIn Connect Tool on LinkedRadar for connecting to relevant people on LinkedIn

If you're not getting interview calls, It's time to upgrade..

Do this and thank me later...

Update LinkedIn ‘Open To Work’ Setting’ with Generic Title (Software Developer) as well as Role specific tile (Python Developer). Select all location types and tech hubs in India. Update your current location to be Bangalore, Hyderabad or Noida bcz most companies hire from these locations.

Go to GeekWire or Product Hunt and Cold dm or email startups founders/directors/CEO/CTO who have raised funds recently with the template I have added in one doc.

 Join Telegram groups where regular job updates are being shared. I have mentioned Arsh Goyal, Kushal Vijay and Go Careers group in the doc.

Build an amazing profile on workatastartup by YC and let companies reach out to you directly.

Bonus : Keep the practice on using the Blind 75 or Neetcode 150 list of questions.

I have collated everything in one doc visit https://bit.ly/10LPAJobPlanKushal

I talked about 7 FREE AI Tools at this University...

If you're a college student, make sure you save this reel and use the tools I talked about in my session.

It was an honor to address the bright minds at K. R. Mangalam University , Thankful to the team and faculties for inviting me for their Roborush Hackathon. ❤️

PhantomBuster - Automate tasks like finding email addresses of hiring managers and startup founders

Hiration - Get a free LinkedIn profile or resume review with actionable tips.

JobScan - Tailor your resume to match specific job descriptions

GeekWire - Best way to find startups which recently got funded.

Copilot - Perfect for answering questions, drafting essays, and coding help.

NapkinAI- Helps you create amazing infographics.

Ideogram - Make amazing thumbnails or posters using a single prompt for free.

Save if you also dream to work at Microsoft ♥️

Hiring Challenges
- Microsoft Explore
Program for 2nd year students for SDE roles at Microsoft. Open to all colleges. I'll share in my community.

- Microsoft Fix-a-thon
Annual Hackathon for hiring Tech Support and Consultant roles. Conducted in Nov-Dec.

- Microsoft Research Fellow and Intern
MSR annually hires Interns from college students or graduates. Conducted mostly during the last quarter of the year.

Roadmap on - github(.)com/KushalVijay/GetHiredRoadmap2024/

Skills Required:
- Data Structures & Algorithms
Mostly asked across all roles. 

- System Design, HLD and LLD
Mostly asked in SDE roles, Difficulty level varies from years of experience.

- DevOps, Cloud & Infra tools
Mostly asked in Support & Consultant roles

- CS Fundamentals

Salary Structure:
- Base Pay
- On Hire Stocks
- Sign On Bonus
- Perks
